The four officers will appear at the Johannesburg Magistrate Court on 17 March 2021 and they are facing chargers of murder, 3 X attempted murder and defeating the end of justice. @eNCA Four police officers have been arrested in connection with the death of Mthokozisi Ntumba. pic.twitter.com/YsPKMmWnoH Ntumba was shot with rubber bullets at close range by police during Wits student protests last week. READ: Grieving Ntumba family want justice The Independent Police Investigative Directorate says the four officers will appear at the Johannesburg Magistrates' Court on Wednesday. They are facing charges of murder, attempted murder and defeating the end of justice.